thread.title: Algerian Military Plane Crashes, Killing at Least 100 People

author: wsjcom
title: Algerian Military Plane Crashes, Killing at Least 100 People
text:
At least 257 people were killed when an Algerian military plane crashed outside the capital, Algiers, on Wednesday morning, the country’s defense ministry said, the world’s deadliest aviation disaster in almost four years and the nation’s worst ever.
The plane plowed into a field at 7:50 a.m. local time shortly after departing Boufarik military air base southwest of the capital, the ministry said. It was bound for Bechar, Algeria, near the Moroccan border, with a stop in Tindouf, the military said.
